    "verdict_rationale": "RLE pre-pass + T4 Huffman (T6) modeled aggregate ratio 0.5974 vs T4 baseline 0.5872 — +1.74% WORSE. T4's order-1 context implicitly exploits runs (any run of identical codes C creates context C->C with near-probability-1, coded near-0 bits). An explicit RLE pre-pass then adds escape-token overhead and expands the alphabet, inflating all context tables in T4 with no offsetting gain on near-singleton streams (text, log_like). For files with real run structure (sparse_clustered), T2 (RLE-codes alone, 178B) already dominates T4 (502B) without needing T4 on top; the composition makes it worse (140B model is worse than T2's 126B model, and T2 actual=178B proves T2 wins cleanly). No corpus file exists where T6 outperforms both T2 and T4. AC-4 Rust implementation is n/a."
